{"title": "Til Murder Do Us Part", "content": "Someone is attempting to kill their spouse (or already has), either to collect on life insurance, because the voices in their head told them to do it, or for some other reason. Maybe they're really a serial killer who marries their victims and then offs them in succession. Or maybe Divorce Requires Death in this setting.\n\nMost often the couple is newly wed, and the unfortunate victim usually won't suspect a thing until after the wedding, when things start to take a turn for the disturbing.\n\nCompare The Bluebeard and Black Widow, who do this over and over again.\n\nA subtrope of Murder in the Family.\n\nA common parody is to have the protagonist think his spouse is trying to do this, often with several Stab the Salad moments.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TilMurderDoUsPart", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheBatmanAdventures", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/RedSonja", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Aladdin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MysteryScienceTheater3000", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheScreamingSkull", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SoIMarriedAnAxeMurderer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePrincessBride", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlfredHitchcock", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Suspicion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MrAndMrsSmith2005", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SonOfDracula", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AdeleHasntHadHerDinnerYet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TalesFromTheCrypt", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheWholeNineYards", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ABrothersPrice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AgathaChristie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheThirteenProblems", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MissMarple", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LordEdgwareDies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DeathOnTheNile", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HerculePoirot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/EvilUnderTheSun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DestinationUnknown", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAn